cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.IR 

The paper presents an approach based on a deep neural network for semantic segmentation of sea-floor images to identify Posidonia oceanica meadows. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image processing and analysis, as well as robotics (RO) for implementing the network in an autonomous underwater vehicle (AUV). The use of a deep neural network also involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The paper also discusses the generation of real-time semantic coverage maps, which could fall under graphics (GR) or information retrieval (IR) categories.
